dc_title_s: West Indies, Cuba, Bahía de Santiago de Cuba (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the Defense Mapping Agency Hydrographic/Topographic Center. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "From a Cuban chart to 1975." "Copyright 1995 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Includes source listing and tidal information. Map no.26224 This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA). United States. Defense Mapping Agency. (1995). West Indies, Cuba, Bahía de Santiago de Cuba (Raster Image). LandInfo. Available at: https://purl.stanford.edu/xs186wf0207 This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
